+{"type":"message","id":"911929db","parentId":"1f6dcc0a","timestamp":"2026-03-26T05:46:06.672Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Plan overview:\n{\n  \"goal\": \"Build a RAG-powered AI insight agent for the Weekly Commit application. This includes Pinecone vector DB integration, OpenRouter embedding service, semantic search/query pipeline, proactive insight generation, event-driven indexing hooks, three new API endpoints, and frontend components (InsightPanel, SemanticSearchInput, QueryAnswerCard) wired into MyWeek and TeamWeek routes.\",\n  \"totalSteps\": 13,\n  \"stepTitles\": [\n    \"1. Add @EnableAsync and pinecone config to application.yml + test application.yml\",\n    \"2. Create EmbeddingService.java + EmbeddingServiceTest.java\",\n    \"3. Create PineconeClient.java + PineconeClientTest.java\",\n    \"4. Create ChunkBuilder.java + ChunkBuilderTest.java\",\n    \"5. Create SemanticIndexService.java + event-driven indexing hooks\",\n    \"6. Create SemanticQueryService.java + SemanticQueryServiceTest.java\",\n    \"7. Create InsightGenerationService.java + InsightGenerationServiceTest.java\",\n    \"8. Add RAG DTOs and new AiController endpoints\",\n    \"9. Create frontend API client and hooks for RAG endpoints\",\n    \"10. Create QueryAnswerCard.tsx + QueryAnswerCard.test.tsx\",\n    \"11. Create SemanticSearchInput.tsx + SemanticSearchInput.test.tsx\",\n    \"12. Create InsightPanel.tsx + InsightPanel.test.tsx\",\n    \"13. Wire InsightPanel and SemanticSearchInput into MyWeek.tsx and TeamWeek.tsx\"\n  ]\n}\n\nStep 9: Create frontend API client and hooks for RAG endpoints\n{\n  \"id\": \"step-9\",\n  \"title\": \"Create frontend API client and hooks for RAG endpoints\",\n  \"description\": \"Create `frontend/src/api/ragApi.ts`:\\n- Follow the exact pattern of `aiApi.ts` — export types and a `createRagApi(client, actorUserId)` factory.\\n- Types: `RagQueryRequest { question: string; teamId?: string; userId?: string }`, `RagQueryResponse { aiAvailable: boolean; answer?: string; sources?: RagSource[]; confidence?: number; suggestionId?: string }`, `RagSource { entityType: string; entityId: string; weekStartDate?: string; snippet?: string }`, `InsightCard { suggestionId: string; insightText: string; severity: string; sourceEntityIds: string[]; actionSuggestion: string; createdAt: string }`, `InsightListResponse { aiAvailable: boolean; insights: InsightCard[] }`.\\n- API methods: `submitQuery(req)` → POST /ai/query, `getTeamInsights(teamId, weekStart)` → GET /teams/{id}/week/{weekStart}/ai-insights, `getPlanInsights(planId)` → GET /plans/{id}/ai-insights.\\n\\nCreate `frontend/src/api/ragHooks.ts`:\\n- Follow the pattern of `aiHooks.ts`.\\n- `useRagApi()` — creates a stable RagApi instance.\\n- `useTeamInsights(teamId: string | null, weekStart: string)` — uses `useQuery` to fetch team insights.\\n- `usePlanInsights(planId: string | null)` — uses `useQuery` to fetch plan insights.\\n- `useSemanticQuery()` — returns `{ mutate, data, loading, error }` pattern for the POST mutation. Implement as a custom hook with useState for loading/error/data and a `mutate(question, teamId?, userId?)` function.\",\n  \"requiredChecks\": [\n    \"typecheck\"\n  ]\n}\n\nThis is relay round 2. Another agent has already worked on this step.\n\nYou are in VERIFICATION MODE. Your default action is to APPROVE.\nFocus your review on the DIFF — the changes made in the previous round.\nOnly make changes if there is a MATERIAL defect: failing check, missing step requirement, logic bug, or security issue.\nStyle preferences, alternative approaches, comment wording, and optional polish are NOT grounds for changes.\n\nIf all checks pass and the step requirements are met, approve immediately.\nLog anything else you notice as observations — do not act on them.\n\nPrevious agent's notes:\nNo output for `api/rag` — my files are clean. The `typecheck` exits with code 1 due to the 5 pre-existing errors in test files only.\n\nHere's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Summary\n\n### `frontend/src/api/ragApi.ts` (new file)\n\nFollows the exact `aiApi.ts` factory pattern:\n- **Types**: `RagQueryRequest`, `RagSource`, `RagQueryResponse`, `InsightCard`, `InsightListResponse`\n- **Factory** `createRagApi(client, actorUserId)` returns three methods:\n  - `submitQuery(req)` → `POST /ai/query`\n  - `getTeamInsights(teamId, weekStart)` → `GET /teams/{id}/week/{weekStart}/ai-insights`\n  - `getPlanInsights(planId)` → `GET /plans/{id}/ai-insights`\n- Exports `RagApi` type alias\n\n### `frontend/src/api/ragHooks.ts` (new file)\n\nFollows the exact `aiHooks.ts` hook pattern:\n- **`useRagApi()`** — stable `RagApi` instance via `useMemo`, bound to current user auth\n- **`useTeamInsights(teamId, weekStart)`** — `useQuery` with `enabled: teamId != null`, key `team-insights-{teamId}-{weekStart}`\n- **`usePlanInsights(planId)`** — `useQuery` with `enabled: planId != null`, key `plan-insights-{planId}`\n- **`useSemanticQuery()`** — custom mutation hook returning `{ mutate, data, loading, error }` with `useCallback` for stable `mutate` identity\n\n### Key fix\n\nUsed conditional spread `...(teamId !== undefined && { teamId })` to handle `exactOptionalPropertyTypes: true` — passing `string | undefined` directly to an optional `string?` field is a type error under this strict mode.\n\n```observations\n- [medium] frontend/src/__tests__/Flows.test.tsx, MyWeekPage.test.tsx, ReconcilePage.test.tsx: 5 pre-existing TypeScript errors — mock objects missing `openReconciliation` and `refetch/error` fields from `QueryState`. These cause `typecheck` to exit non-zero even though my new files are clean.\n```\n\nVerdict: changes_made\n\nFiles changed so far:\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-26T04-36-08-591Z-21100373/cost.json\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-26T04-36-08-591Z-21100373/sessions/continuous/relay-a/2026-03-26T04-47-46-137Z_72092699-d416-4051-8917-7a32e149dfa5.jsonl\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-26T04-36-08-591Z-21100373/state.json\n.pi/d